WESTERN LOAN & BUILDING COMPANY, a Corporation, Appellant, v. Albert C. ARTHUR and H. B. Estes, Appellees. No. 11075. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit Jan. 31, 1946. M. Perelli-Minetti, of Los Angeles, Cal., and H. L. Mulliner, of Salt Lake City, Utah, for appellant. Fred A. Wilson, of San Bernardino, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the motion of appellant for dismissal of the appeal herein, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in this cause be dismissed, with costs in favor of appellees, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
